  "text": "ALDH activity has been applied for identifying CSCs in a variety of tumor types [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . We used the ALDEFLUOR assay to quantitate the percentage of ALDH br cells in xenografted lung tumors (Fig.3A) . In each experiment, the samples were stained simultaneously with Aldefluor and DEAB for identifying the ALDH br population. A subpopulation of ALDH br cells was detected by flow cytometry (1.62% ±0.02% of the total cell population) and was also observed by fluorescent microscopy (Fig. 3B ).",
